  "findings": [
    "The clean-GPU persistent sweep matches the original W7900 per-run sweep within noise; concurrent GPU use was not the source of the low W7900 GGUF prefill number.",
    "Persistent-session mode cuts wall time substantially by loading/repacking once: ~3.60x at 512/128, ~3.18x at 4K/128, ~2.09x at 32K/128, ~1.26x at 128K/128.",
    "Repeated graph capture in one long-lived process caused HIP-internal VRAM growth; retaining/reusing one decode graph fixes the growth and keeps final IDs correct after resetting the full-attention device position scalar before each replay.",
    "The W7900-vs-RX 4K prefill gap is not explained by chunk policy: W7900 no-chunk 4K Q4_K_S is 1711 tok/s vs RX final-gate 2723 tok/s. It is also not explained by clocks: during no-chunk 4K, sampled SCLK reaches 2984 MHz, MCLK 1124 MHz, FCLK 2301 MHz.",
